value.value: This gene regulates the G1/S phase of the cell cycle by cyclin expression.
This gene is involved in the regulation of intestinal cell processes that are affected by vasoactive intestinal peptides.
G1/S-specific cyclin-E1 (401 aa, ~47 kDa) is encoded by the human CCNE1 gene. This protein is involved in the progression of the cell cycle between the G1 and S phases.
DNA-(apurinic or apyrimidinic site) lyase (318 aa, ~36 kDa) is encoded by the human APEX1 gene. This protein plays a role in both DNA repair and the regulation of transcription.
This gene plays a role in histone-lysine methylation.
This gene plays a role in signal transduction and intercellular signaling. It is involved in the modulation of bone turnover.
This gene plays a role in mitochondrial function, postnatal skeletal growth and cartilage homeostasis.
This gene plays a role in signal transduction and intercellular communication. It is involved in the growth of progenitor cells during embryogenesis.
Adjuvants used in surgical procedures.
This gene plays a role in signal transduction and intercellular communication. It is involved in short-range signaling in pattern formation during embryonic development.
This gene plays a role in signal transduction and intercellular communication. It is involved in the regulation of cell fate and pattern formation during embryo development.

Apurinic/apyrimidinic (AP) sites occur frequently in DNA molecules by spontaneous hydrolysis, by DNA damaging agents or by DNA glycosylases that remove specific abnormal bases. AP sites are pre-mutagenic lesions that can prevent normal DNA replication so the cell contains systems to identify and repair such sites. Class II AP endonucleases cleave the phosphodiester backbone 5' to the AP site. (From LocusLink 27301)
DNA-(apurinic or apyrimidinic site) lyase 2 (518 aa, ~57 kDa) is encoded by the human APEX2 gene. This protein is involved in DNA repair.
This gene plays a role in signal transduction, cell organization and intercellular communication. It is involved in development of the heart, kidneys, lungs and skeleton.
This gene plays a role in signal transduction and intercellular communication. It is involved in the regulation of cell behavior and fate during vertebrate development.
This gene is involved in cell-mediated immunity and differentiation.
This gene is involved in chemotaxis and G protein-coupled receptor signal transduction.
This gene plays a role in apoptosis and intercellular communication.
This gene is involved in signal transduction and cell cycle control. It also plays a role in the inhibition of apoptosis.
An angiogenesis inhibitor that acts by inhibiting the growth, migration, and proliferation of endothelial cells and/or induces endothelial cell apoptosis.
Serine/threonine-protein kinase ATR (2644 aa, ~301 kDa) is encoded by the human ATR gene. This protein plays a role in protein phosphorylation, DNA repair and cell cycle progression.
This gene plays a role in transcription and is postulated to regulate cellular responses to growth factors.
This gene plays a role in transcriptional activation in response to cytoskeletal changes and inhibits cellular proliferation.
This gene plays a role in transcriptional activation and DNA binding interactions.
Interleukin-27 receptor subunit alpha (636 aa, ~69 kDa) is encoded by the human IL27RA gene. This protein is involved in both interleukin-27 signaling and Th1-type immune responses.
Tyrosine-tRNA ligase, cytoplasmic (528 aa, ~59 kDa) is encoded by the human YARS1 gene. This protein is involved in the attachment of tyrosine to its cognate tRNA.
DNA excision repair protein ERCC-1 (297 aa, ~33 kDa) is encoded by the human ERCC1 gene. This protein plays a role in 5-prime incision during both UV cross-link repair and nucleotide excision repair.

DNA Repair Endonucleases specifically catalyze the hydrolysis of interior DNA phosphodiester bonds during correction of errors in DNA structure and sequence to protect genetic information against chemical, radiation or spontaneous damage and against replication errors, and to restore DNA to its original state.
Ubiquitin carboxyl-terminal hydrolase 6 (1406 aa, ~159 kDa) is encoded by the human USP6 gene. This protein is involved in both protein deubiquitination and vesicle trafficking.

An angiogenesis inhibitor that acts by blocking the action of endothelial integrins.  An endothelial-specific integrin/survival signaling inhibitor binds to and blocks the activity of endothelial-specific integrins, thereby inhibiting endothelial cell-cell interactions, endothelial cell-matrix interactions, and angiogenesis.
Ubiquitin carboxyl-terminal hydrolase 8 (1118 aa, ~128 kDa) is encoded by the human USP8 gene. This protein plays a role in both protein deubiquitination and the inhibition of protein degradation.
Vascular endothelial growth factor C (232 aa, ~27 kDa) is encoded by the human VEGFC gene. This protein is involved in both cell proliferation and angiogenesis.

Vasoactive intestinal peptide (28 aa, ~3 kDa) is encoded by the human VIP gene. This protein is involved in vasodilation, arterial blood pressure, glycogenolysis, stimulation of myocardial contractility, and relaxation of the smooth muscles of the trachea, stomach and gall bladder.

Vasoactive intestinal polypeptide receptor 1 (457 aa, ~52 kDa) is encoded by the human VIPR1 gene. This protein plays a role in G protein-coupled receptor signaling, digestion, muscle contraction and the regulation of cell proliferation.

Guanine nucleotide exchange factor VAV3 (847 aa, ~98 kDa) is encoded by the human VAV3 gene. This protein plays a role in guanine nucleotide exchange for transforming protein RhoA, Rho-related GTP-binding protein RhoG, and Ras-related C3 botulinum toxin substrate 1.
WNT1-inducible-signaling pathway protein 2 (367 aa, ~40 kDa) is encoded by the human CCN5 gene. This protein may play a role in bone turnover.

label.value: General Transcription and DNA Repair Factor IIH Helicase Subunit XPD

value.value: General transcription and DNA repair factor IIH helicase subunit XPD (760 aa, ~87 kDa) is encoded by the human ERCC2 gene. This protein plays a role in DNA helicase activity, RNA polymerase II-mediated transcription and nucleotide excision repair.

Cellular communication network factor 6 (354 aa, ~39 kDa) is encoded by the human CCN6 gene. This protein plays a role in mitochondrial electron transport and mitochondrial respiration and the maintenance of skeletal bone and cartilage.
Protein Wnt-2b (391 aa, ~44 kDa) is encoded by the human WNT2B gene. This protein plays a role in binding to receptors of the frizzled family to stimulate signaling pathways.
Protein Wnt-6 (365 aa, ~40 kDa) is encoded by the human WNT6 gene. This protein plays a role in signaling during embryonic development.
Protein Wnt-10a (417 aa, ~46 kDa) is encoded by the human WNT10A gene. This protein is involved in signal transduction through binding to frizzled family receptors.
Protein Wnt-11 (354 aa, ~39 kDa) is encoded by the human WNT11 gene. This protein is involved in binding to and stimulating signaling by frizzled family receptors.

label.value: TFIIH Basal Transcription Factor Complex Helicase XPB Subunit

value.value: TFIIH basal transcription factor complex helicase XPB subunit (782 aa, ~89 kDa) is encoded by the human ERCC3 gene. This protein is involved in RNA polymerase II-mediated transcription, DNA helicase activity and nucleotide excision repair.
Protein Wnt-9a (365 aa, ~40 kDa) is encoded by the human WNT9A gene. This protein is involved in the positive regulation of frizzled family receptor-dependent signaling.
Histone-lysine N-methyltransferase NSD2 (1365 aa, ~152 kDa) is encoded by the human NSD2 gene. This protein is involved in both histone methylation and transcriptional regulation.
14-3-3 protein theta (245 aa, ~28 kDa) is encoded by the human YWHAQ gene. This protein is involved in adaptor signaling protein activity.
Zinc finger protein 36, C3H1 type-like 2 (494 aa, ~51 kDa) is encoded by the human ZFP36L2 gene. This protein is involved in the regulation of mRNA stability.

label.value: Zinc Finger and BTB Domain-Containing Protein 17

value.value: Zinc finger and BTB domain-containing protein 17 (803 aa, ~88 kDa) is encoded by the human ZBTB17 gene. This protein is involved in the modulation of both transcription and the cell cycle.
